==English==
===Etymology===
Probably from {{OE.}} ''[[scylfe]]'' (deck of a ship); distantly related to ''[[sculpt]]'', "[[carve]]" and ''[[shell]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʃɛlf/}}
*{{audio|en-us-shelf.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛlf|-ɛlf]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|shelves}}

# A [[flat]], [[rigid]], [[rectangular]] [[structure]], [[fixed]] at [[right angle]]s to a [[wall]], and [[used]] to [[support]], [[store]] or [[display]] [[object]]s.
# The [[capacity]] of such an object; as, a shelf of videos.
# A [[projecting]] [[ledge]] that resembles such an object.
# A [[reef]], [[shoal]] or [[sandbar]].

====Synonyms====
*(''capacity''): [[shelfful]]

====Derived terms====
*[[continental shelf]]
*[[off the shelf]]
*[[on the shelf]]
*[[shelfful]]

